    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "31. wiser than all men—that is, all his contemporaries, either at home or abroad.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "than Ethan—or Jeduthun, of the family of Merari (1Ch 6:44).",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Heman—(1Ch 15:17-19)—the chief of the temple musicians and the king's seers (1Ch 25:5); the other two are not known.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "the sons of Mahol—either another name for Zerah (1Ch 2:6); or taking it as a common noun, signifying a dance, a chorus, \"the sons of Mahol\" signify persons eminently skilled in poetry and music.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
